track_notes: This was a really nice hike.  It is longer than the usual SOTA hike, and you only get 6 points, but it is well worth doing.  There were a few points where I almost wanted to skip the radio part and go explore some of the red rock cliffs!  The first 3.1 miles are on single track hiking trail and most of the climbing comes after mile 2.  Once you reach the  ridge, it changes to double track ATV road.  The next 1.5 miles drop down into the bowl, then climb back up.  At around 4.6 miles, there is a sign for a road 9952A, veering off towards the summit, but this path vanishes almost immediately and you will have to bushwhack the final 0.6 miles up.  I took different paths going up versus down, and neither was any better.  The bushwhack is very rocky and grasses hide the rocks, making for tricky footing.  The summit provides incredible views including the famous Sedona geological features as well as Humphreys Peak off in the distance.
track_title: House Mountain via Turkey Creek Trail
